There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.2.0 out of 5 starsLost me half way through the book.ByBoyMomx3on May 6, 2013Format: Paperback|Verified PurchaseI got the Kindle version of Forsaken, and I am glad I did not pay more than $1.99 for it, it just was not worth it. The book's plot idea was captivating for the first half and then it died. The author then slowly builds up another plot only to again end it really quickly. It should have been two seperate books, neither plot got a chance to become fully developed. I also felt that some of the way the author dealt with faith issues were wishy-washy at best, and intially I would have rated this book a one, but he redeemed himself in the end. Great ideas, just a very disjointed ride.0Comment|Was this review helpful to you?YesNoReport abuseCommentInsert product linkPaste the product's web address below:Product not found. Only products offered on Amazon can be linked.SelectWhat's this?What are product links?In the text of your review, you can link directly to any product offered on Amazon.com. To insert a product link, follow these steps:1. Find the product you want to reference on Amazon.com2. Copy the web address of the product3. Click Insert product link4. Paste the web address in the box5. Click Select6. Selecting the item displayed will insert text that looks like this: 
