There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.5.0 out of 5 starsForsaken, by James David JordanBycoupecheveuxon December 20, 2014Format: Kindle Edition|Verified PurchaseA great book I believe, different yes, but something that could very well happen to us, if God forbid we are left behind, and have to go through the Tribulation, or simply to go through such an ordeal and to decide  the fate of one of our children, by either renounce our faith in God, that there is no such a God. Or keep our faith and our child would live.  It makes one think deeply. I have thought about these things before, and have to remember that those kind of people would be very evil, and therefore could not be trusted to let the child or whoever live. We are to put our love in God first, before our loved ones, hard, yes but we would be together in the end, in a glorious place. This story is well put together, and is meant to make us think: what would we do? Yes, I would recommend this book to others, I am now looking for another one from this author.0Comment|Was this review helpful to you?YesNoReport abuseCommentInsert product linkPaste the product's web address below:Product not found. Only products offered on Amazon can be linked.SelectWhat's this?What are product links?In the text of your review, you can link directly to any product offered on Amazon.com. To insert a product link, follow these steps:1. Find the product you want to reference on Amazon.com2. Copy the web address of the product3. Click Insert product link4. Paste the web address in the box5. Click Select6. Selecting the item displayed will insert text that looks like this: 
